https://github.com/lorenzofox3/Smart-Table/issues/196 ,https://github.com/lorenzofox3/Smart-Table/issues/196.

Basically
1) map/clean your collection before you bind it to smart table
```Javascript
$scope.rowCollection = data.map(d=>Object.assign({},{propWanted:d.propWanted, ... });
```
2) or use a custom filter which map for you depending on whatever condition you want to use
```Javascript
function customFilter(array, predicateExpression){
   const searchable = data.map(d=>Object.assign({},{propWanted:d.propWanted, ... });
   return $filter('filter')(searchable,predicateExpression);
}
```

