For anything where the count is more than the records, it just gives whatever it can grab, so if there are 5 records and I ask for 10, it gives only 5 back. We use this fact to perform our paging, checking that the number of records returned matches the number we asked for, and if so, shifting the offset until we get a less than full set of data. I believe there is just not data returned if you use an offset larger than the number of records.

Regarding grabbing the second batch of 2000 records (specifically 2001-4000), you would use a count of 2000 and an offset of 2000. The offset is strictly the number of records to skip, so to get all records you will need to start from 0. You can see how we normally grab all records by looking at the [`_iterate()`](https://github.com/charlesthk/python-mailchimp/blob/master/mailchimp3/baseapi.py#L36-L73) command that is used when an `all()` function is called with `get_all=True` set.

@charlesthk, do you think it would be a good idea to drop the iteration value from 5k to 1k since this may be an issue of timing out or something similar, or do you have any ideas on testing that case?

For anyone looking for a solution, it is not possible with stock django admin. Please see this function that handles the closing popup [here](https://github.com/django/django/blob/b99221b8bb2a4cd7fd5ac6e5f03e8eb1953d6384/django/contrib/admin/static/admin/js/admin/RelatedObjectLookups.js#L76).

So I overrode the function.

`javascript
if (!$) {
    $ = django.jQuery;
    function dismissAddRelatedObjectPopup(win, newId, newRepr) {
        var name = windowname_to_id(win.name);
        var elem = document.getElementById(name);

        if (elem) {
        	// here is our customization
        	// if this is present, the plugin is present
        	$select = $('.searchable-select#' + name + '-chips');
        	if($select){

                var $chips = $('#' + name + '-chips');
                var $chip = $('<div/>').addClass('chip minimized').html(newRepr).append(
                    $('<input/>').attr('type', 'hidden').attr('name', $select.attr('data-name')).attr('value', newId)
                );
                $chips.append($chip);
                window.setTimeout(function () {
                    $chip.removeClass('minimized');
                }, 0);

        	} else {
        		// Everything else from here on is identical to the latest compatible version 
	            if (elemName === 'SELECT') {
	                elem.options[elem.options.length] = new Option(newRepr, newId, true, true);
	            } else if (elemName === 'INPUT') {
	                if (elem.className.indexOf('vManyToManyRawIdAdminField') !== -1 && elem.value) {
	                    elem.value += ',' + newId;
	                } else {
	                    elem.value = newId;
	                }
	            }
	            // Trigger a change event to update related links if required.
	            $(elem).trigger('change');
        	}
        } else {
            var toId = name + "_to";
            var o = new Option(newRepr, newId);
            SelectBox.add_to_cache(toId, o);
            SelectBox.redisplay(toId);
        }
        debugger;
        win.close();
    }
}
`

