I didn't understand your point about why you would have to reset variables. 

Lists are a bit problematic. Currently Sacred offers no good way of modifying config entries that are lists. The workaround that I currently use is to instead use dictionaries with meaningless keys. E.g.
```python
@ex.config
def cfg():
    layers = {
        '1': (100, 'relu'),
        '2': (200, 'tanh')
     } 
``` 
This allows modifying the "list" of layers normally at the cost of some clarity a bit of tediousness when using it later. Note that you can use integer keys, but it is not recommended, since it interacts badly with the commandline.

